MapCSS is a CSS-like language for map stylesheets. This repository handles the specification. Feel free to raise an issue or suggest an improvement by creating a pull request.

* [http://www.mapcss.org/ MapCSS website]
* [http://lists.openstreetmap.org/listinfo/mapcss MapCSS Mailing list at mapcss@openstreetmap.org]

* [[specification.mediawiki|Specification]]

== List of software supporting MapCSS ==
* [http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Halcyon Halcyon] (flash-based renderer)
* [http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Kothic Kothic] (python/cairo based renderer, regexp-based parser)
* [http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Ceyx Ceyx] (python/cairo based renderer)
* [http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Potlatch Potlatch] (online flash-based editor)
* [http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/JOSM JOSM] (offline Java-based editor; [https://help.openstreetmap.org/questions/22384/highlight-untagged-and-unconnected-nodes-in-a-way example])
* [http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Kothic_JS Kothic JS] (javascript/HTML5-based renderer)
* [http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Komap Komap] (mapnik stylesheet preprocessor)
* [http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Tcl-OSM Tcl-OSM] (parser)
* [https://github.com/Gubaer/dart-mapcss dart-mapcss] - provides an [http://www.antlr.org/ antlr] grammar for MapCSS and a generated lexer/parser in googles [http://www.dartlang.org Dart] programming language
* [http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/overpass_turbo#Styling overpass turbo] (data mining tool based on Overpass API) [http://www.openstreetmap.org/user/tyr_asd/diary/19043 More information]
* [https://github.com/plepe/pgmapcss PGMapCSS] (Runtime CSS evaluation in PostgreSQL; for use with Mapnik)
